  "prompt": "I have a very old account in central bank in which no mobile number is registered. How to register my mobile number now?",
  "response": "To register your mobile number with your central bank account, you can typically follow these steps:\n\n1. Visit the bank branch in person:\n- Carry your identification proof (Aadhar card, PAN card, passport)\n- Account passbook or account details\n- Request to update mobile number in your account\n\n2. Online method:\n- Log into your net banking account\n- Go to profile/personal details section\n- Select option to update contact information\n- Enter new mobile number\n- Complete verification process (might require OTP)\n\n3. Alternative online methods:\n- Download bank's mobile app\n- Use NETBANKING portal\n- Visit bank's official website\n- Use internet banking credentials to update mobile number\n\n4. Written request:\n- Write a formal application requesting mobile number registration\n- Submit at bank branch with necessary identity documents\n\n5. Through customer care:\n- Call bank's customer support number\n- Request mobile number registration\n- Follow their specific procedure\n\nRequired documents:\n- Valid identity proof\n- Address proof\n- Recent passport size photograph\n- Original account documents\n\nPro tip: Carry original and photocopy of identification documents when visiting branch.\n\nAlways confirm exact procedure with your specific bank branch or customer care.",
